article.headline: Texas-Pan American 77, Texas A&amp,M International 61
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Jared Maree scored a season-high 22 points to lead Texas-Pan American to a 77-61 win over Texas A&M International on Saturday night. The Broncs (3-8) led by just two points early in the second half but used a 15-4 run to pull ahead. Most of Maree's scoring, including a trio of 3-pointers that helped the Broncs to a 16-2 run, came in the first half. Brandon Provost helped out Texas-Pan American with 15 points while Aaron Urbanus added 14 and Ruben Cabrera 12. The Dustdevils (6-4) were led by Scottie Payne, who finished with 15 points. Evan Matteson added 14 points and Ryan McLucas 10 for Texas A&M International.
